The night of my high school graduation, my family had gone out for dinner. Afterwards, my mom and I were going to get gas in the car while everyone else was home. She went to the liquor store next door and bought a bottle. I forget the brand but we sat in the parking lot drinking the bottle and enjoying our last summer before I left the nest.
